      <h2>Support contact</h2>
      <p>For reproducible bugs and development tasks, <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/issues">open a GitHub issue</a>. For other questions, email <a href="mailto:support@blockiversevr.com">support@blockiversevr.com</a>.</p>
      <p>When reporting an issue, include your device model, app version or build source, what you expected, what happened instead, and steps to reproduce.</p>

      <h2>Community and development</h2>
      <p>Use the <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/wiki">wiki</a> for documentation and guides. Use <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/discussions">GitHub Discussions</a> for Q&amp;A, gameplay feedback, Quest setup help, feature ideas, and community build reports. Use <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/issues">GitHub Issues</a> for reproducible bugs or scoped development tasks.</p>

      <h2>Known current limitations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Blockiverse VR is in active development and is not a final store release.</li>
        <li>Primary supported hardware is Meta Quest 3 and Meta Quest 3S with Quest Touch controllers.</li>
        <li>Multiplayer is local LAN only. Cloud-hosted private worlds are tracked as future expansion work.</li>
        <li>Worlds are bounded rather than infinite streaming terrain.</li>
        <li>Voice communication uses Meta Quest party chat. There is no in-app voice chat.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Before reporting</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/wiki">wiki</a>, <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/issues">existing issues</a>, and <a href="https://github.com/eslutz/Blockiverse-VR/discussions">discussions</a> to see if the problem is already known or answered.</li>
        <li>Restart the headset and confirm the issue happens again.</li>
        <li>Note whether you were in creative, survival, or LAN multiplayer.</li>
        <li>For LAN multiplayer issues, include host/client device models and whether both devices were on the same local network.</li>
        <li>For save/load issues, avoid deleting local app data until the save can be inspected or backed up.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
